author: Jesse Pound
title: California sees one million unemployment claims in less than two weeks
description: There have been one million unemployment claims in California since March 13, Gov. Gavin Newsom said.
content:
California Gov. Gavin Newsom said Wednesday that the state has seen one million unemployment claims in less than two weeks as the coronavirus pandemic has led to businesses being shutdown across the state.
